# =============================================================================
# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# --------------------
# Each non-comment line is a CVE ID that trivy will skip when scanning go.mod.
# Remove a CVE entry here once the underlying dependency has been upgraded to
# the patched version and `go mod tidy` has been run.
#
# =============================================================================
# github.com/docker/docker — CVE-2026-34040 (HIGH) & CVE-2026-33997 (MEDIUM)
# =============================================================================
#
# WHY THESE ARE IGNORED
# ---------------------
# Both CVEs affect the Docker daemon's authorization-plugin model:
#
#   CVE-2026-34040 (HIGH)   – Authorization bypass that allows an API caller to
#                             circumvent Docker daemon authorization plugins.
#                             Patched in docker/docker v29.3.1.
#
#   CVE-2026-33997 (MEDIUM) – Privilege-validation bypass during Docker plugin
#                             installation. No upstream fix published yet at the
#                             time of writing.
#
# WHY WE CANNOT FIX THEM NOW
# ---------------------------
# docker/docker v29.3.1 (the patched release) has not been published to the Go
# module proxy as of 2026-05-15.  Running `go get github.com/docker/docker@v29.3.1`
# returns "invalid version: unknown revision v29.3.1".
#
# docker/docker is an INDIRECT dependency, pulled in transitively by
# testcontainers-go (used only for integration tests that spin up real DB and
# messaging containers locally). lib-commons itself never embeds or runs a
# Docker daemon; the Go client library merely calls the Docker API from test
# code. The authorization-bypass risk described in both CVEs is therefore
# contained entirely within local developer/CI test environments and does not
# affect lib-commons consumers in production.
#
# WHAT TO DO WHEN docker v29 IS RELEASED
# ----------------------------------------
# 1. Remove the two lines below (CVE-2026-34040 and CVE-2026-33997).
# 2. Run:  go get github.com/docker/docker@v29.3.1
# 3. Run:  go mod tidy
# 4. Verify trivy reports zero findings:  trivy fs --scanners vuln go.mod
#
CVE-2026-34040
CVE-2026-33997

# =============================================================================
# github.com/docker/docker — CVE-2026-41567, CVE-2026-42306, CVE-2026-41568
# =============================================================================
#
# WHY THESE ARE IGNORED
# ---------------------
# These CVEs affect Docker daemon archive/copy endpoints:
#
#   CVE-2026-41567 (HIGH)   – PUT /containers/{id}/archive may execute container
#                             payloads during archive extraction.
#
#   CVE-2026-42306 (HIGH)   – Race condition in docker cp can allow bind mount
#                             redirection.
#
#   CVE-2026-41568 (MEDIUM) – Race condition in docker cp can allow archive
#                             creation in an unintended location.
#
# WHY WE CANNOT FIX THEM NOW
# ---------------------------
# Trivy reports no fixed version for github.com/docker/docker v28.5.2 as of
# 2026-05-18. We upgraded testcontainers-go from v0.41.0 to v0.42.0 and ran
# go mod tidy, but the latest published testcontainers release still resolves
# github.com/docker/docker v28.5.2+incompatible.
#
# docker/docker is an INDIRECT dependency, pulled in transitively by
# testcontainers-go for integration tests. lib-commons itself does not embed or
# run a Docker daemon in production, and the affected Docker archive/copy paths
# are not part of the library runtime surface.
#
# WHAT TO DO WHEN A FIXED VERSION IS RELEASED
# -------------------------------------------
# 1. Remove the three lines below.
# 2. Upgrade testcontainers-go and/or github.com/docker/docker to the patched
#    version published upstream.
# 3. Run:  go mod tidy
# 4. Verify trivy reports zero findings:  trivy fs --scanners vuln .
#
CVE-2026-41567
CVE-2026-42306
CVE-2026-41568
